TY  - JOUR
AU  - Williamson, Stephen D.
T1  - Increasing Returns to Scale in Financial Intermediation and the Non-Neutrality of Government Policy
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297723
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 53
IS  - 5
SP  - 863
EP  - 875
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - A general equilibrium model of imperfectly competitive financial intermediaries is constructed and used to study the effects of some standard policy experiments. One-time increases in the growth rate and in the level of the stock of money have non-neutral (and sometimes surprising) effects on interest rates, the quantity of intermediated borrowing and lending, the number of intermediary firms, inflation and the price level. Optimal government macroeconomic policy is shown to reflect a tradeoff between public sector frictions and the capital market distortion created by increasing returns to scale and imperfect competition in private intermediation.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297723
ER  - 



