TY  - JOUR
AU  - Azariadis, Costas
AU  - Guesnerie, Roger
T1  - Sunspots and Cycles
PY  - 1986
Y1  - 1986/10/01
DO  - 10.2307/2297716
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 53
IS  - 5
SP  - 725
EP  - 737
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - Because sunspot equilibria seem to be of central importance for an understanding of rational expectations, we seek here to characterize completely a limited class of sunspot equilibria (stationary ones with two possible natural events) in the simplest overlapping generations model of production. We present a sufficient condition for the existence of stationary sunspot equilibria, examine how these are related to strictly periodic equilibria of the same order, and investigate how deterministic stationary equilibria bifurcate to stationary sunspot equilibria. A concluding section examines how our results survive in more general settings.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2297716
ER  - 



